children.value: Correcting Issues
Step 1
The first step would be to
Auto fix
the:
Failed Tags
Language
Title
Asking Adobe Acrobat Pro to fix something automatically, means you are requesting
Adobe Acrobat Pro to guess at the layout of your document and code it accordingly.
Using the Auto fix, you will never end up with a 100% correct document. The
percentage will depend on the document's content, and usually, it's anywhere
between 85% and 95% accurate. So there will always be something for you to edit
manually.
Step 2
Because you have Auto Tagged the documented, not
every tagged heading will be a heading, not every
tagged image will be an image and not every tagged
Table will be a table!
So you should expand all errors and click on each one
to check within the document that they have been
correctly tagged.
Quick check of Tags
Adobe's Accessibility checker may not identify all the issues that the document may
have. Everything may be coded technically correct and in sequence, but until you
confirm that something is actually a header, or a table, etc., you can't say the
document is accessible.
To check that everything is coded correctly, you will need to go into the
Tags
and click
on every heading, Table and figure tag to review the document.
